# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  AI Agent Tutorial — Environment Configuration
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  HOW TO USE
#  ----------
#  1. Copy this file:  cp .env.example .env
#  2. Fill in ONE provider's API key (the one you want to use).
#  3. Set PROVIDER below to match.
#  4. Run any chapter — `shared/config` will read .env and wire up the
#     correct base_url / api_key / model automatically.
#
#  THE ONE-LINE PROVIDER SWITCH
#  ----------------------------
#  All providers speak the OpenAI-compatible API. That means a SINGLE
#  library (the `openai` SDK) can talk to all of them — only the
#  `base_url` and `model` change. Changing the PROVIDER line below
#  reroutes every request in the whole tutorial.
#
#      PROVIDER=openai      → OpenAI official
#      PROVIDER=deepseek    → DeepSeek
#      PROVIDER=qwen        → Alibaba Qwen (DashScope)
#      PROVIDER=ollama      → Local Ollama (free, offline, no API key)
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  ACTIVE PROVIDER  ← change this ONE line to switch everything
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PROVIDER=openai


# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Provider 1/4 — OpenAI  (https://platform.openai.com/)
#  Get a key at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#  Default model: gpt-4o-mini
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key-here


# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Provider 2/4 — DeepSeek  (https://www.deepseek.com/)
#  Get a key at: https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
#  base_url: https://api.deepseek.com/v1
#  Default model: deepseek-chat
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-your-deepseek-key-here


# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Provider 3/4 — Qwen / DashScope  (https://dashscope.aliyun.com/)
#  Get a key at: https://dashscope.console.aliyun.com/apiKey
#  base_url: https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1
#  Default model: qwen-plus
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-your-dashscope-key-here


# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Provider 4/4 — Ollama  (https://ollama.com/)  — LOCAL, FREE
#  Install Ollama, then pull a model:
#      ollama pull qwen2.5:7b
#  Ollama needs NO real API key — any non-empty string works.
#  base_url: http://localhost:11434/v1
#  Default model: qwen2.5:7b
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OLLAMA_API_KEY=ollama   # not strictly required; config uses a dummy


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  OPTIONAL OVERRIDES  (leave commented to use each provider's default)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Override the model name for the active provider if you like:
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o
# DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-reasoner
# QWEN_MODEL=qwen-max
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1:8b
